Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Zest
and quarter @lemon{1%unit} (quarter both lemons for 4 servings). Thinly slice
@chili pepper{1%unit}, removing seeds for less heat.

Once water is boiling, add @gemelli pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente,
~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ¾ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then
drain.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking
up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir half the @Tuscan heat spice{1%tablespoon} (use all for 4 servings), half the
lemon zest, and a pinch of chili and @salt{pinch} (we used ½ tsp; use ¾ tsp for
4) into pan with sausage. Cook, stirring, ~{30 seconds to 1%minute}.

Stir ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water (¾ cup for 4 servings) and juice from 1
lemon wedge (2 wedges for 4) into same pan. Bring mixture to a simmer, scraping
up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Turn off heat; stir in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon},
half the @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup} (you'll use the rest later), and salt. Cook,
stirring, until smooth.

Stir gemelli, @peas{6%ounce}, and @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings)
into pan with sauce until peas are warmed through and butter is melted. If
needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water 1 TBSP at a time until pasta is
coated in a creamy sauce. Season with salt and @pepper{}. Divide between bowls.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan, lemon zest, and chili if desired. Serve with
remaining lemon wedges on the side.